<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12177c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12177c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12177c"> 177(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Pison / Gihon / Hiddekel / Euphrates</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;And a river went out of Eden to water the garden; and from thence it was parted, and became into four heads. <mark>The name of the first river is Pison, and the name of the second river is Gihon, and the name of the third river is Hiddekel, and the fourth river is the Euphrates</mark>.&rdquo; &mdash; Moses. <small> Standish O'Grady, <a name="OGSE" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#OGSE"><cite title="source">Selected Essays and Passages</cite></a> (1918) 78 [O&apos;Grady quoting the Old Testament as a motto for a sub-chapter, called <i>The Nuts of Knowledge</i>]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The four rivers of Eden (see <cite>Genesis</cite> 2: 10-14). </mm> </dd></dl>
